cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a computer vision task of face parsing using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new framework that extends the iCNN model, which involves training multiple CNNs in an interlinked manner. This makes it likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The paper also deals with image processing and modification, which falls under the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper involves training the model end-to-end, which involves optimizing the model's parameters using backpropagation, making it likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
